						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab from Olyappa's Maṭha now kept in the house of Mr. W.T. Apte.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1082.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">[Dundubhi], Chaitra, ba. 5, Monday, Vishuva-saṁkrānti, Solar eclipse.</hi> Obviously the eclipse could not have occurred on the given <hi rend="italic">tithi.</hi> On grounds of palaeography the date may be equated with <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1082 March 21, Monday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">saṁkrānti</hi> did not occur on that day.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land to god Uttarēśvara of <hi rend="bold">Jaṁbukhaṇḍi.</hi> The beginning of the record is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
